principalDf = pd.DataFrame(data = principalComponents, columns = ['principal components 1', 'principal components 2'])

In [21]:
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
%matplotlib inline

fig = plt.figure(figsize = (8,8))
ax = fig.add_subplot(1,1,1)
ax.set_xlabel('principal component 1' , fontsize =15)
ax.set_ylabel('principal component 2' , fontsize =15)
ax.set_title('2 component PCA' ,fontsize =15)
targets = ['age' ,'anaemia','creatinine_phosphokinase','diabetes','ejection_fraction','high_blood_pressure','platelets',
           'serum_creatinine','serum_sodium' , 'sex', 'smoking', 'time']
colors= ['red','green','blue','black','yellow','pink','orange','brown','grey' ,'purple','silver','gold']
for target,color in zip(targets,colors):
    indicesToKeep = finalDf['DEATH_EVENT']==target
    ax.scatter(finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep,'principal components 1']
               ,finalDf.loc[indicesToKeep,'principal components 2']
               ,c = color
               ,s = 50)
ax.legend(targets)
ax.grid()

In [23]:
import warnings  
warnings.simplefilter('ignore')

Error = [] 
for i in range(1, 11):
    kmeans = KMeans(n_clusters = i).fit(x2)
    kmeans.fit(x2)  
    Error.append(kmeans.inertia_)  
plt.plot(range(1, 11), Error)
plt.title('Elbow method')
plt.xlabel('No of clusters')
plt.ylabel('Error')
plt.show()
